headline: Private-Equity Deals Are on Pace for Bumper Year
summary: The September quarter featured the richest stretch of private-equity deal activity in years, with big-ticket transactions such as the $55 billion buyout of videogame company Electronic Arts.    The quarter’s estimated 5,083 deals brought this year’s tally to 15,107 deals worth around $1.
